to the editor re zimbabwe press law criticized world briefing feb 6 and zimbabwe tightens curbs on media and foreign journalists news article feb 1 the main objection to the bill centered on its provisions for the regulation of the media there is nothing undemocratic in having legal regulation of any profession all countries have laws requiring the registration and licensing of practitioners of different professions on zimbabwe many reporters appear keen to reflect only their country 's foreign policy and not on providing the correct information the law has nothing to do with next month 's presidential elections since it will not be in force for at least three months it is the right of all zimbabweans to criticize the content of any bill but the final arbiters are the elected representatives of the people of zimbabwe their voice should be respected simbi v mubako ambassador of zimbabwe washington feb 11 2002

